              African Grey Parrot Lifespan
            </h1>
            <p class="font-sora mx-auto mt-4 max-w-xl text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-white/85 md:mx-0 md:text-base">A Congo African Grey commonly lives <strong>50 to 60 years or more</strong> in captivity, and a Timneh just as long — decades beyond most dogs and longer than many marriages.</p>
            <p class="font-sora mx-auto mt-4 max-w-xl text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-white/85 md:mx-0 md:text-base">Here at C.A.Gs in Midland, Texas, Mark &amp; Teri Benjamin have hand-raised captive-bred Congo and Timneh Greys since 2014, and this guide lays out exactly how long an African Grey lives, what makes that number rise or fall, and why a Grey is a 40-to-60-year commitment worth planning for before you ever bring one home.</p>
            <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3 md:justify-start">
              <a href="#how-long" class="font-sora rounded-full bg-clay px-7 py-3.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white transition-colors hover:bg-clay-dk">How Long Do They Live? →</a>
              <a href="#commitment" class="font-sora rounded-full border-2 border-white/60 px-7 py-3.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white transition-all hover:border-white hover:bg-white hover:text-green">The 40–60 Year Reality →</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- CIRCULAR IMAGE STAGE -->
